article.headline: Yale 57, Brown 55
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. -- Ross Morin scored 20 points and grabbed 10 rebounds to lead Yale over Brown 57-55 in an Ivy League contest Friday. The win was Yale?s fifth in a row and second straight against Brown in a week?s time. Yale improved to 7-9 and 2-0 in the Ivy League for the first time since 2002. Alex Zampier added 12 points for the Bulldogs. Matt Mullery paced Brown (6-10, 0-2) with 22 points and 9 rebounds. Adriam Williams added 16 points. Brown had the ball for the final 18 seconds with a chance to tie the game but never got a shot off.
